Dear senior political science student of The University of La Verne<br>
Vietnam Veterans:<br><br>
The African American Soldier in the Vietnam War, particularly in relationship to how he/she was/is portrayed in the media. <br>
You are looking for information regarding Post War Vietnam Veterans.  You may find one of the best places to look would be your Local VA Hospital.  However try to be sensitive about bring up those old war feelings.  You will find that some of the vets have extreme sociological problems and are still shell shocked.  I have found a grate deal of anger comes from the us involvement in that war.  I have also found that people are angry at the fact some of the corporation selling arm or fuel to both sides of the war is an other subject of grate frustration.  So temper your question with sensitivity regarding Vietnam.  <br><br>
I was not a vet in the Vietnam era but I am a vet and I know a lot of vet who were.  Also check your county wide phone directory for Veterans Of Post War organizations you might find what your looking for there.  Good luck!<br><br>
Respectfully yours<br><br>
B.J.<br>

